-- Amazon pays IBM to settle patent litigation
-- 
-- Tue May 8, 2007 9:32am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/05/08/us-amazon-ibm-patents-idUSWNAS026720070508

 

 BOSTON  (Reuters) - Amazon.com Inc. ( AMZN.O ) and International Business Machines Corp. ( IBM.N ) said on Tuesday that they have settled all existing patent litigation between them and signed a long-term intellectual property cross-licensing agreement. 

 The two companies said that Amazon paid an undisclosed amount of money to IBM.